nstraints:**\n\n- The number of nodes in the tree is in the range `[1, 10⁴]`.\n\n- `-1000 <= Node.val <= 1000`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/boundary-of-binary-tree/","problemName":"Boundary of Binary Tree","problemNumber":545,"problemSlug":"boundary-of-binary-tree","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":545,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Dynamic Programming","Memoization"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given several `boxes` with different colors represented by different positive numbers.\n\nYou may experience several rounds to remove boxes until there is no box left. Each time you can choose some continuous boxes with the same color (i.e., composed of `k` boxes, `k >= 1`), remove them and get `k * k` points.\n\nReturn *the maximum points you can get*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: boxes = [1,3,2,2,2,3,4,3,1]\nOutput: 23\nExplanation:\n[1, 3, 2, 2, 2, 3, 4, 3, 1] \n----> [1, 3, 3, 4, 3, 1] (3*3=9 points) \n----> [1, 3, 3, 3, 1] (1*1=1 points) \n----> [1, 1] (3*3=9 points) \n----> [] (2*2=4 points)","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: boxes = [1,1,1]\nOutput: 9","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: boxes = [1]\nOutput: 1","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= boxes.length <= 100`\n\n- `1 <= boxes[i] <= 100`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Dynamic Programming","Memoization"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Hard","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given several `boxes` with different colors represented by different positive numbers.\n\nYou may experience several rounds to remove boxes until there is no box left. Each time you can choose some continuous boxes with the same color (i.e., composed of `k` boxes, `k >= 1`), remove them and get `k * k` points.\n\nReturn *the maximum points you can get*.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: boxes = [1,3,2,2,2,3,4,3,1]\nOutput: 23\nExplanation:\n[1, 3, 2, 2, 2, 3, 4, 3, 1] \n----> [1, 3, 3, 4, 3, 1] (3*3=9 points) \n----> [1, 3, 3, 3, 1] (1*1=1 points) \n----> [1, 1] (3*3=9 points) \n----> [] (2*2=4 points)\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: boxes = [1,1,1]\nOutput: 9\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: boxes = [1]\nOutput: 1\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= boxes.length <= 100`\n\n- `1 <= boxes[i] <= 100`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-boxes/","problemName":"Remove Boxes","problemNumber":546,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given several `boxes` with different colors represented by different positive numbers.\n\nYou may experience several rounds to remove boxes until there is no box left. Each time you can choose some continuous boxes with the same color (i.e., composed of `k` boxes, `k >= 1`), remove them and get `k * k` points.\n\nReturn *the maximum points you can get*.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: boxes = [1,3,2,2,2,3,4,3,1]\nOutput: 23\nExplanation:\n[1, 3, 2, 2, 2, 3, 4, 3, 1] \n----> [1, 3, 3, 4, 3, 1] (3*3=9 points) \n----> [1, 3, 3, 3, 1] (1*1=1 points) \n----> [1, 1] (3*3=9 points) \n----> [] (2*2=4 points)","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: boxes = [1,1,1]\nOutput: 9","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: boxes = [1]\nOutput: 1","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= boxes.length <= 100`\n\n- `1 <= boxes[i] <= 100`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Hard","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given several `boxes` with different colors represented by different positive numbers.\n\nYou may experience several rounds to