:564,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given a string `n` representing an integer, return *the closest integer (not including itself), which is a palindrome*. If there is a tie, return ***the smaller one***.\n\nThe closest is defined as the absolute difference minimized between two integers.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: n = \"123\"\nOutput: \"121\"","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: n = \"1\"\nOutput: \"0\"\nExplanation: 0 and 2 are the closest palindromes but we return the smallest which is 0.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n.length <= 18`\n\n- `n` consists of only digits.\n\n- `n` does not have leading zeros.\n\n- `n` is representing an integer in the range `[1, 10¹⁸ - 1]`.","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Hard","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"Given a string `n` representing an integer, return *the closest integer (not including itself), which is a palindrome*. If there is a tie, return ***the smaller one***.\n\nThe closest is defined as the absolute difference minimized between two integers.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: n = \"123\"\nOutput: \"121\"\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: n = \"1\"\nOutput: \"0\"\nExplanation: 0 and 2 are the closest palindromes but we return the smallest which is 0.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n.length <= 18`\n\n- `n` consists of only digits.\n\n- `n` does not have leading zeros.\n\n- `n` is representing an integer in the range `[1, 10¹⁸ - 1]`.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-closest-palindrome/","problemName":"Find the Closest Palindrome","problemNumber":564,"problemSlug":"find-the-closest-palindrome","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":564,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Depth-First Search"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array `nums` of length `n` where `nums` is a permutation of the numbers in the range `[0, n - 1]`.\n\nYou should build a set `s[k] = {nums[k], nums[nums[k]], nums[nums[nums[k]]], ... }` subjected to the following rule:\n\n- The first element in `s[k]` starts with the selection of the element `nums[k]` of `index = k`.\n\n- The next element in `s[k]` should be `nums[nums[k]]`, and then `nums[nums[nums[k]]]`, and so on.\n\n- We stop adding right before a duplicate element occurs in `s[k]`.\n\nReturn *the longest length of a set* `s[k]`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [5,4,0,3,1,6,2]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: \nnums[0] = 5, nums[1] = 4, nums[2] = 0, nums[3] = 3, nums[4] = 1, nums[5] = 6, nums[6] = 2.\nOne of the longest sets s[k]:\ns[0] = {nums[0], nums[5], nums[6], nums[2]} = {5, 6, 2, 0}","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [0,1,2]\nOutput: 1","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] < nums.length`\n\n- All the values of `nums` are **unique**.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Depth-First Search"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given an integer array `nums` of length `n` where `nums` is a permutation of the numbers in the range `[0, n - 1]`.\n\nYou should build a set `s[k] = {nums[k], nums[nums[k]], nums[nums[nums[k]]], ... }` subjected to the following rule:\n\n- The first element in `s[k]` starts with the selection of the element `nums[k]` of `index = k`.\n\n- The next element in `s[k]` should be `nums[nums[k]]`, and then `nums[nums[nums[k]]]`, and so on.\n\n- We stop adding right before a duplicate element occurs in `s[k]`.\n\nReturn *the longest length of a set* `s[k]`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [5,4,0,3,1,6,2]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: \nnums[0] = 5, nums[1] = 4, nums[2] = 0, nums[3] = 3, nums[4] = 1, nums[5] = 6, nums[6] = 2.\nOne of the longest sets s[k]:\ns[0] = {nums[0], nums[5], nums[6], nums[2]} = {5, 6, 2, 0}\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [0,1,2]\nOutput: 1\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] < nums.length`\n\n- All the values of `nums` are **unique**.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/array-nesting/","problemName":"Array Nesting","problemNumber":565,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an integer array `nums` of length `n` where `nums` is a permutation of the numbers in the range `[0, n - 1]`.\n\nYou should build a set `s[k] = {nums[k], nums[nums[k]], nums[nums[nums[k]]], ... }` subjected to the following rule:\n\n- The first element in `s[k]` starts with the selection of the element `nums[k]` of `index = k`.\n\n- The next element in `s[k]` should be `nums[nums[k]]`, and then `nums[nums[nums[k]]]`, and so on.\n\n- We stop adding right before a duplicate element occurs in `s[k]`.\n\nReturn *the longest length of a set* `s[k]`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [5,4,0,3,1,6,2]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: \nnums[0] = 5, nums[1] = 4, nums[2] = 0, nums[3] = 3, nums[4] = 1, nums[5] = 6, nums[6] = 2.\nOne of the longest sets s[k]:\ns[0] = {nums[0], nums[5], nums[6], nums[2]} = {5, 6, 2, 0}","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [0,1,2]\nOutput: 1","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] < nums.length`\n\n- All the values of `nums` are **unique**.","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Medium","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"You are given an integer array `nums` of length `n` where `nums` is a permutation of the numbers in the range `[0, n - 1]`.\n\nYou should build a set `s[k] = {nums[k], nums[nums[k]], nums[nums[nums[k]]], ... }` subjected to the following rule:\n\n- The first element in `s[k]` starts with the selection of the element `nums[k]` of `index = k`.\n\n- The next element in `s[k]` should be `nums[nums[k]]`, and then `nums[nums[nums[k]]]`, and so on.\n\n- We stop adding right before a duplicate element occurs in `s[k]`.\n\nReturn *the longest length of a set* `s[k]`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [5,4,0,3,1,6,2]\nOutput: 4\nExplanation: \nnums[0] = 5, nums[1] = 4, nums[2] = 0, nums[3] = 3, nums[4] = 1, nums[5] = 6, nums[6] = 2.\nOne of the longest sets s[k]:\ns[0] = {nums[0], nums[5], nums[6], nums[2]} = {5, 6, 2, 0}\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [0,1,2]\nOutput: 1\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 10⁵`\n\n- `0 <= nums[i] < nums.length`\n\n- All the values of `nums` are **unique**.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/array-nesting/","problemName":"Array Nesting","problemNumber":565,"problemSlug":"array-nesting","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":565,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":10061,"contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0566-reshape-the-matrix/566-reshape1-grid.jpg","originalUrl":"../../../images/566-reshape1-grid.jpg","sha256":"e46b89739fb7fc5751e5435ec61592b291b39c46709881f7c6162cb229525821"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":9512,"contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0566-reshape-the-matrix/566-reshape2-grid.jpg","originalUrl":"../../../images/566-reshape2-grid.jpg","sha256":"a539664fd7fe702c3d20cc2237596fe27f6b8683013b9230bc8bfa54bff6f1f0"}],"categories":["Array","Matrix","Simulation"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"In MATLAB, there is a handy function called `reshape` which can reshape an `m x n` matrix into a new one with a different size `r x c` keeping its original data.\n\nYou are given an `m 